It is an abtraction( instane ) which either consume( read) or produce( write ) information from
source to destination.

Stream is always associated with resource.

Standard stream instances of Java programming languages which are associated with
Console( Keyboard / Monitor ):
System.in
System.out
System.err


output stream This abstract class is the superclass of all classes representing an output stream of bytes. 
An output stream accepts output bytes and sends them to some sink.

input stream : This abstract class is the superclass of all classes representing an input stream of bytes.
